      "writtenOn": "2019-07-31T21:27:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m still thinking about it. I want as much of the state as possible to be specified in some repository (so we have history and code review and BUG\u003d... references and Revert button, etc).\n\nIf not using Spinnaker:\n  * Images are tagged with unique immutable tags that identify their origin (I\u0027m planning to use \"\u003cdate\u003e_\u003ccommitposition\u003e_\u003ccommit\u003e\", e.g. \"20190731_24797_a365bd5c\", \u003cdate\u003e is for eyeballing by humans, \u003ccommitposition\u003e is for sorting within a day, \u003ccommit\u003e is just for easier mapping back into git).\n  * k8s manifests use these tags to refer to images, not \"floating\" tags like \u0027stable\u0027 or \u0027latest\u0027.\n  * k8s manifests live in a separate repo. There\u0027s post commit builder that deploys them on each commit.\n  * There\u0027s an auto-roller that takes a tag of latest produced image and commits it as a version to use for -dev cluster (thus kicking off the rollout).\n  * Prod versions are updated manually (i.e. by manual commit to the repository with k8s configs).\n\nIf using Spinnaker: needs more research.",
