    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7f76470b_be76c71e",
        "filename": "results/deployment.yaml",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 103,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-31T21:27:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We have two choices:\n\n1. Standardize on GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS and disable all other ways LUCI server picks up credentials, such us using developer tokens (via `luci-auth login`) or using Swarming task accounts.\n2. Do not use GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS at all, and write server code to use luci-go auth library to pick up the default credential.\n\nThe reason is that GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS is picked up by Google Cloud libraries by default. But these Cloud libraries are unable to use any other form of authentication when running locally (unlike LUCI libraries). If we standardize on GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS, but not set it when running stuff locally, LUCI libraries *will* work, but native Cloud libraries *will not* work, and this is kind of random. They all either should work (will happen with choice 2), or neither of them should work (will happen with choice 1).\n\nI personally much prefer 2, but I can be convinced to drop support for running as developer locally and switch to 1.\n\n----\n\nI assume GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS was chosen here because Spanner client is initialized as\n\n  spanner.NewClient(ctx, \"\u003cdb\u003e\")\n\nIf we want to follow (2), it should be\n\n  ts, err :\u003d auth.GetTokenSource(ctx, auth.AsSelf, auth.WithScopes(spanner.Scope))\n  ...\n  spanner.NewClient(ctx, \"\u003cdb\u003e\", option.WithTokenSource(ts))\n\n(where \u0027auth\u0027 is https://godoc.org/go.chromium.org/luci/server/auth)",
      "parentUuid": "a9d86855_2113d919",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 103,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 103,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "9925ebcfe929c0c07d96d9cddcecfd69b1052d66",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "762bed90_5c7b366a",
        "filename": "results/deployment.yaml",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 103,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-01T16:52:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if by GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS you mean making sure it is not in the env, then I agree. Specifically, I\u0027d like to avoid two auth mechanisms at the same time. If we have both explicitly passed creds and the env variable, then it is easy to accidentally not wire a spanner client (or any other client) to the explicitly passed creds. This mistake would be left unnoticed, until someone tries to run that locally.\n\nSo I think we should inline the env variable, at the very least.\n\nNow one more question unrelated to this CL: Vadim, how can we reduce duplication in other GKE apps? It seems that all deployment.yaml files will have to have this line. Are you thinking of solving this with kustomize? I.e. ideally there is only one place where implements passing of the creds.",
      "parentUuid": "7f76470b_be76c71e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 103,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 103,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "9925ebcfe929c0c07d96d9cddcecfd69b1052d66",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
